{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6858ffdc-475f-4b31-94f8-3b90a555c9da","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Install the .NET 11 SDK locally (`dotnet --version` to confirm).\n- Run `dotnet restore` to update dependencies.\n- Check for breaking changes in the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) and update any deprecated APIs.\n- Build and test: `dotnet build && dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"99c5bdf8-7301-4548-8b1c-2ada799e21c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no tools needed.","outputTokens":279,"requestId":"B414:180EFF:8E34CF:B023FB:6A0135D1"},"id":"2d5be4e4-2214-465b-bd20-c865b2075898","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:50:15.313Z","parentId":"5ddb27ef-4340-4544-b3d0-295c7c862a29"}
